# Cross-Layer Contract Sync

- Treat `backend/app/schemas.py`, `frontend/src/api/types.ts`, and `frontend/src/hooks/useStream.ts` as one contract surface.
- When API payloads, SSE events, or endpoint inputs change, update the mirrored frontend types and consumers in the same change.
- When adding backend capabilities that surface in the UI, wire them through the typed client in `frontend/src/api/client.ts`.

## Required Patterns

- Keep `delta`, `meta`, `final`, and `error` stream events compatible with `useStream`.
- Update frontend request/response types when backend Pydantic models or route payloads change.
- Add or update focused tests when contracts or stream behavior change.

## Prohibited Patterns

- No backend-only contract changes that leave frontend types or stream handling stale.
- No ad hoc fetch calls that re-declare request or response shapes already owned by `api/client.ts` and `api/types.ts`.
